reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are very nice
reviews.reviewText: You will not be disappointed if you purchase these. They are well made and are very attractive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These are nice quality artificial plants. The containers are a durable metal and the jute twine bows add a nice rustic touch. These look great on the table with my tiered tray and other rustic farmhouse decor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I so wanted to love these. I have to agree they are cute. Especially the little pails. However all overshadowed by the excessive amount of “flocking” on these plants. Like someone took a bag of confectioners sugar and dumped it on the 3 of them. The plant portions are shipped individually sealed to prevent loss but they can afford it. So much more than a few flakes on the table. Excuse me now while (achewww) I grab the vacuum. These are for black shelving and will never work for me. It only makes them look dusty/dirty. It’s way Beyond the fuzz look you get w a real plant. I would rub it off and clean them up but I don’t want to take the chance that I still won’t like them and then ruin them for the next person they’ll send my return to. They missed the mark on my set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: cute, and glad there's no possible way for me to kill them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Dusty, but Super Cute
reviews.reviewText: Okay, so these have white powder / frosting on the leaves for a certain look; however, it goes everywhere when you touch the plants. I suggest using a hand-vac to suck up any loose debris.Other than that, these are really cute! They look good sitting out on top of my shelves. They don't look fake unless you're up really close with them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute, Durable, Affordable
reviews.reviewText: Got these for our outdoor patio, and they look fantastic. Even after a full summer of wind, rain, and sun...they still look like new!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great value and they look great in my house, giving it a true farmhouse feel. I love how real they look and how good they look on my tables. So far everyone who has came to visit has complemented me on my gardening skills, little do they know its fake!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Makes me laugh
reviews.reviewText: When we got the plants they had some kind of white power on them. After my wife cleaned them off and sort of polished them up she placed them outside. She put them strategically on the porch you have to notice them. We have a flower garden that brings color and sweet smells up to the house. People who come to the house comment on the garden as they walk up the driveway. When they get to the porch they look at the fake plants and believe they are real. Most of them walk up to one to smell. We get, Hay these are not real!! They look real but have no smell!! I laugh and ask, Are we in trouble for that??
